# Fog regression gate

Read `tools/FOG_REGRESSION.md` before editing fog.

## Required before editing fog

1. Post **Self-Correction Step** per [coding-safety.mdc](../coding-safety.mdc) (regression traps + perf implications + minimal diff).
2. Read `tools/FOG_REGRESSION.md` and preserve wiring invariants below.

## Required before marking fog work done

1. Run `.tools/run_fog_smoke.ps1` (or task **fog-smoke**) — must exit 0.
3. Commit **atomic set** together when changing presentation: `.gdshader` + `FogOverlay.gd` + `FogOverlay.tscn` (+ `MainSandbox.gd` if paths/bootstrap change).

## Forbidden

- `git checkout HEAD --` a single fog file without the rest of the atomic set
- Moving `FogOverlay.gd` onto `FogRect` or binding `MainSandbox` to `$FogOverlay/FogRect`
- Transparent `FogRect.color` (breaks shader alpha)
- Relying on `*Into` byte[] interop without `*Native` assign — see `src/Godot/Interop/INTEROP.md`

## WIRING INVARIANT

`FogOverlay.gd` on **CanvasLayer** `$FogOverlay`; material on child `$FogRect` only. `FogOverlay.validate_host_node()` must pass.

## Symptom → first check

| Symptom | Check |
|---------|--------|
| White screen | Godot console `SHADER ERROR`; `FogRect.color` white; shader compiles |
| All black fog | `$FogOverlay` vs `$FogOverlay/FogRect`; bootstrap / mask interop |
| Hard edges / speckles | mask `filter_nearest` + graded stamps; not binary `FillRevealedMask` alone |
| Zoom clip / tiny disc | `ensure_buffer_for_current_zoom` recenter; buffer edge vs live disc |
